valueString.value: General screening test in urine for controlled substances and drugs of abuse.

valueMarkdown.value: Note that the terminologies included in this implementation guide will need to be updated, because the ideal mechanism for distribution (as an expression) is not currently supported by the content logical definition constructs available in the FHIR ValueSet resource and all known implementations of it. Before use in a production environment, ensure you have the latest value sets based on the definitions for each value set (as defined in the inclusion/exclusion criteria for each one).

publisher.value: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)

description.value: ValueSet containing all general screening tests in urine for drugs of abuse other than narcotics codes.

display.value: Clinical Focus

text.value: General screening tests in urine for drugs of abuse other than narcotics.

display.value: United States of America

purpose.value: Used to determine if patient has urine screening for drugs of abuse other than narcotics for recommendation 10.

valueString.value: set delimiter = " "; set axis = "Multiaxial Parent Of"; FROM [^LOINC^] with (CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF "Controlled substances and drugs of abuse (LP31448-1)[LOINC]" AND ^System[LOINC]^ EQUALS "Urine") AND_NOT CONCEPT DESCENDANT_OF "Narcotics and opioids (LP18149-2)[LOINC]" EXPORT ^Name^,^Code^,^Component[LOINC]^,^has element[LOINC]^;
